==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Catskill period
<hw>Cats"kill pe`ri*od</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>The
closing subdivision of the Devonian age in America. The rocks of this
period are well developed in the Catskill mountains, and extend south
and west under the Carboniferous formation. See the Diagram under
<er>Geology</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catso</ent>⟦br⟧
